Some group of concern persons in Sokoto have frowned at the purported plot by the federal government of Nigeria to bring doctors from China to help combat the covid-19 pandemic. The group which consist of several human rights activists, CSOs and medical related NGOs urged the Nigerian government to show appreciation to home grown professionals. Speaking on the trending subject of FG bringing doctors from China, a human rights activists and development social strategists, Ibrahim Adamu Tudun Doki said, no patriotic Nigerian will ever welcome such decision. According to Ibrahim, Nigeria has professionals across the globe that have excelled in their respective profession. Tudun Doki, the activists, said, it practically unethical for the government to pay our doctors who despite all challenges agreed to put their lives on the line to safe the country on several occasions including the deadly convict 19 pandemic. He further submitted that, if the federal government refused to reverse it’s alleged plans of bringing doctors from China, then it should be noted that, the same government that is spearheading the patronage of made in Nigeria is discouraging people from patriotism. Tudun Doki also assured that, the current morales of the Nigerian doctors that are sacrificing to treat patients of convict 19 should not be dampened by any idea that tends to discredit their competencies in the face of non availability of modern medical facilities. Speaking on his part, one of the medical personnel who spoke on condition of anonymity said, they will be left with no option that to embark on massive strike in the event FG went ahead with its plan to bring doctors from China over the Covid-19 pandemic. 